column5: Been waiting for a chance to be fishing,It was a perfect day outside. Bluebird skies, no wind, decent ice, but the perch weren't so co-operative. Spent the day in the harbour waiting on some finicky fish. Even so we patiently dangled our baits down the hole and were rewarded. A lot of dinks, but still had enough decent volunteers for dinner.
Nice feed, looking to bring a bunch of perch home tomorrow. What was your biggest perch?  Thanks for sharing, MTBF

You did better than me today Bruce Got to old skunk in again.... that was strike three and that lake is out Will have to try so familiar grounds next time around Your volunteers look prime Thanks for sharing Jacques
